							Minimum Government Fees</td><td>US$300
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Registered Office Required</td><td>Yes
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Registered Agent Required</td><td>Yes – Cook Islands trustee company
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							How long does it take to form</td><td>3-5 business days
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Residency & qualification of Council Members</td><td>No restriction on residence. Person must not be disqualified from managing companies under Cook Islands domestic or international companies legislation.
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Number of Council Members</td><td>Minimum 1 natural person or 1 corporate entity
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Number of Officers</td><td>Not applicable in Cook Islands
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Secretary</td><td>Not required, however the foundation must have a Cook Islands trustee company as Registered Agent
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Protector / Enforcer (Guardian)</td><td>Optional (A person cannot be both a Council Member and Enforcer)
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Publicly available information at 	Registry</td><td>Certificate of Registration and 	Charter*
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							*Charter Requirements (the Foundation Instrument)</td><td>1) To be filed with registered agent & Registry</p>
							<p>2) Not mandatory to include details of founder, council members or beneficiaries (all of whom are named in the Rules†)</p>
							<p>3) Instrument must specify name, objects and the registered agent.
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							†Regulations/Articles (supporting Charter – similar to Trust document)</td><td>
							<p>1) Private & not filed at Registry</p>
							<p>2) Rules contains details of Founder, Beneficiary, Council Members and Enforcer</p>
						</td>
					<tr>
					</tr>
						<td>
							Anti-forced heirship provisions</td><td>Yes
						</td>
					</tr>
